\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. GEPHYROIDES Babcock. Glabrous or pubescent perennials or biennials with taproots; stems with few branches. Lower leaves petiolate, denticulate to dentate or subpinnatifid. Capitula with many florets. Ligules yellow, sometimes reddish-purple on outer face. Receptacle with glabrous or ciliate pits.
\par 

