\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. CREPIS. Pubescent or glabrescent perennials or biennials with woody taproots; stems with few to many branches. Lower leaves petiolate, denticulate to pinnatifid. Capitula with few to many florets. Ligules yellow, sometimes reddish-purple on outer face, rarely purplish-pink. Receptacle usually with more or less densely ciliate, rarely glabrous, pits.
\par 

